.TH TSPDF 1 "2026" "tspdf" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tspdf \- local-first PDF toolkit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tspdf
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tspdf
merges, splits, encrypts, watermarks, compresses and otherwise manipulates
PDF files, entirely on the local machine. No network access, no dependencies.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B merge
Merge multiple PDF files into one.
.TP
.B split
Split a PDF into individual pages or ranges.
.TP
.B rotate
Rotate pages in a PDF.
.TP
.B delete
Delete pages from a PDF.
.TP
.B reorder
Reorder pages in a PDF.
.TP
.B encrypt
Encrypt a PDF with a password.
.TP
.B decrypt
Decrypt a password-protected PDF.
.TP
.B metadata
View or edit PDF metadata.
.TP
.B info
Print information about a PDF.
.TP
.B watermark
Add a text or image watermark to a PDF.
.B \-\-text
draws a diagonal text stamp;
.B \-\-image
draws a PNG/JPEG with
.B \-\-scale
and
.BR \-\-position .
.TP
.B stamp
Overlay a page of another PDF onto pages of the input (like pdftk stamp).
.B \-\-under
puts it beneath the existing content.
.TP
.B pagenum
Stamp page numbers on a PDF.
.B \-\-pages
limits which pages are stamped.
.TP
.B compress
Compress a PDF to reduce file size.
.TP
.B text
Extract text from a PDF to stdout or a file.
.B \-\-pages
selects pages;
.B \-\-layout
preserves the page layout (columns and tables stay aligned).
.TP
.B form
List, fill, or flatten AcroForm form fields.
.B form list
prints the fields as JSON;
.B form fill
takes a JSON object
.RB ( \-\-data )
and/or repeated
.B \-\-set
.I name=value
pairs;
.B form flatten
stamps the values into the page content and removes the form.
.TP
.B attach
Embed files in a PDF, or list, extract, or remove embedded files
.RB ( "attach add" / list / extract / remove ).
.TP
.B img2pdf
Convert images (JPEG/PNG) to a PDF.
.B \-\-page\-size
chooses a4, letter, or a page sized to each image.
.TP
.B qrcode
Generate a QR code PDF.
.TP
.B md2pdf
Convert Markdown to a styled PDF.
.TP
.B serve
Start a local web server for PDF tools (default port 8080, bound to
127.0.0.1; change with
.B \-\-port
and
.BR \-\-bind ).
.PP
Run
.B tspdf help
.I command
for command-specific options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Show the help message.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
tspdf merge a.pdf b.pdf \-o combined.pdf
tspdf split report.pdf \-\-pages 1\-5 \-o extract.pdf
tspdf encrypt doc.pdf \-o locked.pdf \-\-password secret
tspdf watermark doc.pdf \-o draft.pdf \-\-text "DRAFT"
tspdf form fill form.pdf \-\-set name=Ada \-o filled.pdf
tspdf watermark doc.pdf \-o marked.pdf \-\-image logo.png \-\-opacity 0.2
tspdf stamp report.pdf \-\-stamp approved.pdf \-o stamped.pdf
tspdf serve \-\-port 3000
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qpdf (1),
.BR pdftk (1)
.PP
